WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:05.010
Tell me, your dreams, am I in them?

00:05.160 --> 00:07.811
- So how do we do this?
- I have so much to teach you.

00:07.960 --> 00:10.611
I'm the most important relationship
in your life.

00:10.760 --> 00:11.966
You're a disease.

00:12.120 --> 00:14.122
Tomorrow when they kill you, I'll be cured.

00:14.320 --> 00:17.164
Ryan Hardy declined your invitation
to attend your execution.

00:17.320 --> 00:19.163
- Must be some mistake.
- I'm afraid not.

00:19.320 --> 00:21.368
I don't wanna lose you.
I'm gonna do better.

00:21.520 --> 00:23.170
I'll be out in a minute.

00:23.320 --> 00:25.800
- Where's Penny?
- She's been gone several days.

00:26.000 --> 00:27.923
WESTON:
Why hit the office of Strauss' paralegal?

00:28.080 --> 00:29.923
RYAN:
There's something hidden there we missed.

00:30.080 --> 00:33.323
- I'm in.
- Strauss used a code to protect his secrets...

00:33.480 --> 00:36.848
...that can only be deciphered
using a key phrase chosen by the creator.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.684
I think Strauss entrusted you.

00:38.840 --> 00:41.844
You give me what I want,
I will punish Ryan Hardy for both of us.

00:42.040 --> 00:43.246
Ryan Hardy...

00:43.400 --> 00:45.084
...belongs to me.

00:45.240 --> 00:46.287
I'm sorry, Theo.

00:46.480 --> 00:50.724
I'm not ready to pass on the torch
while I still have a card left to play.

00:54.800 --> 00:56.290
[CHATTERING]

01:36.240 --> 01:37.685
[KEYS JINGLING]

01:46.480 --> 01:48.687
Welcome to the last day of your life.

01:52.280 --> 01:54.009
[DOOR CLOSES]

02:02.480 --> 02:04.642
This is a day many thought
would never come.

02:04.800 --> 02:08.327
Joe Carroll, the murderous cult leader
responsible for killing dozens...

02:08.520 --> 02:11.763
...while terrorizing the country
is due to be executed tonight at midnight.

02:11.920 --> 02:12.967
[PHONE RINGING]

02:13.120 --> 02:15.043
It was over a year ago
that Carroll's reign...

02:15.200 --> 02:18.966
...of terror was finally brought to an end
by FBI agent Ryan Hardy.

02:19.120 --> 02:21.930
Since his recapture,
Carroll's been kept in an undisclosed...

02:22.120 --> 02:23.167
You're pretty popular.

02:23.320 --> 02:26.210
Every reporter in the universe
is calling asking for a comment.

02:26.360 --> 02:29.887
I'm actually hoping Theo's cyber-attack
shuts my phone down.

02:31.240 --> 02:33.720
I couldn't sleep so... Breakfast.

02:33.920 --> 02:36.002
Might be a little cold.

02:36.200 --> 02:39.204
REPORTER [ON TV]:
...under constant surveillance.

02:39.520 --> 02:43.764
Our source inside the prison confirms
Carroll has no visitors scheduled.

02:43.960 --> 02:45.689
Even Ryan Hardy has declined...

02:45.840 --> 02:47.842
...to attend his execution.

02:48.800 --> 02:49.926
- Hey.

02:50.080 --> 02:53.562
Why are you doing this to yourself?
You should try and forget about it.

02:54.360 --> 02:56.488
I know, easier said than done.

02:56.640 --> 02:58.642
But seriously...

02:58.800 --> 03:00.006
Skip work.

03:00.200 --> 03:02.521
- Let's go see a movie.
- That's a really nice idea.

03:02.720 --> 03:05.564
I think I would be climbing the walls
inside of five minutes.

03:06.480 --> 03:08.323
I gotta keep busy.

03:12.480 --> 03:14.687
I'll call you later.

03:16.960 --> 03:18.530
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

03:24.320 --> 03:27.164
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

03:33.160 --> 03:38.007
Ah. Ms. Thompson, are you
the cruise director for today's execution?

03:38.160 --> 03:40.447
The court asked me
to make sure your rights...

03:40.600 --> 03:42.887
...are protected
during the execution process.

03:43.040 --> 03:46.010
Otherwise, I'd be watching from home
with a bowl of popcorn.

03:46.200 --> 03:49.443
Tell me, is this the first time
you're witnessing...

03:49.840 --> 03:52.684
...a death up close?
- Yes.

03:52.840 --> 03:55.650
Don't be surprised if
you get a little, uh...

03:55.800 --> 03:56.881
...turned on.

04:12.880 --> 04:14.370
Good morning, gentlemen.

04:14.560 --> 04:15.925
GARZA:
D-day, Joe.

04:16.079 --> 04:17.524
Got my eye on your cell.

04:17.880 --> 04:21.362
Sadly for you, it is
reserved for celebrities...

04:21.600 --> 04:24.490
...not plebeian killers with mommy issues.

04:24.840 --> 04:27.880
You're the one who's gonna be crying
for his mama when those chemicals go in.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.809
[INMATES SHOUTING
AND BANGING ON DOOR]

04:30.720 --> 04:33.405
- Hey, what's the pool up to?
- Fifteen hundred.

04:33.560 --> 04:34.641
What pool?

04:36.240 --> 04:37.730
SLOAN:
How long it'll take Joe to die.

04:38.200 --> 04:40.646
Over-under four minutes.
You want in on it?

04:42.040 --> 04:44.520
I'll pass. So where are we at with Theo?

04:44.720 --> 04:46.961
He's the one who got Gary
posted on death row.

04:47.120 --> 04:50.681
Cyber found the door he used to hack
into the prison sewer. They closed it.

04:50.840 --> 04:52.763
Why do you think Theo reached out to Joe?

04:52.920 --> 04:55.241
Ruining my credit
isn't gonna satisfy him for long.

04:55.440 --> 05:00.685
He's ready to come after me, and smart
enough to know he'll need help to survive.

05:48.760 --> 05:50.967
What the hell are you doing with her?

05:51.160 --> 05:53.003
I asked you a question.

06:00.440 --> 06:02.727
You need to think hard
about this moment, son.

06:04.520 --> 06:06.568
Your whole life has led up to it.

06:06.760 --> 06:08.250
Two roads face you.

06:08.400 --> 06:11.165
One stretches into the distance,
call that enlightenment.

06:11.320 --> 06:15.291
Rehab, career, family.

06:15.560 --> 06:17.608
The other one ends in about 10 seconds.

06:18.720 --> 06:20.529
That one's simply called death.

06:21.440 --> 06:24.205
[GRUNTING]

06:40.560 --> 06:42.130
BRADLEY:
Good morning, Joe.

06:42.640 --> 06:46.361
- Who's your friend?
- Jim Vail, the governor's chief of staff.

06:46.520 --> 06:50.366
And I'm here to make sure
your execution goes off without a hitch.

06:50.520 --> 06:53.808
Oh, I'm sure it'll play big
in the governor's upcoming campaign.

06:53.960 --> 06:56.804
Oh, how about I endorse him
with my final words?

06:57.520 --> 06:59.966
- For God sakes, don't do that.
BRADLEY: Let's get started.

07:04.480 --> 07:06.244
I'm gonna let you out of the chair.

07:06.440 --> 07:09.887
Try anything, and Officer Price is gonna
light you up with his stun baton.

07:10.040 --> 07:11.280
Come on, guys.

07:11.440 --> 07:15.365
Don't make me file a petition with the
court for cruel and unusual punishment.

07:16.360 --> 07:17.441
[GRUNTS]

07:18.840 --> 07:20.285
[STUN BATON CRACKLES]

07:20.800 --> 07:22.006
GUARD:
No wait, stop!

07:22.640 --> 07:24.961
Now, hold on, hold on. Aah!

07:25.120 --> 07:26.326
On the floor.

07:26.560 --> 07:28.164
[ALARM BUZZING]

07:28.320 --> 07:29.401
Now!

07:46.720 --> 07:50.441
You didn't think killing me
was gonna be easy, did you?

07:56.720 --> 07:58.722
- How bad?
- It's a nightmare.

07:58.880 --> 08:01.929
He killed two guards, locked himself in.
He's got three hostages...

08:02.120 --> 08:06.045
...including the governor's chief of staff.
We're gearing our SORT team to go in.

08:06.200 --> 08:09.249
You do that and Joe starts killing people,
the VIP will be first.

08:09.400 --> 08:12.404
The longer we wait, the more time
he has to barricade himself in.

08:12.560 --> 08:14.722
CARROLL:
Good morning, warden. As you can see...

08:14.880 --> 08:17.406
...I have rescheduled today's activities.

08:17.600 --> 08:20.968
And I would hate to be interrupted
by the riot squad who I can see...

08:21.120 --> 08:23.327
...quite clearly on the security monitor.

08:23.760 --> 08:27.401
So all prison personnel
must therefore pull back...

08:27.560 --> 08:29.608
...from this cell block immediately.

08:29.760 --> 08:32.808
And if they don't, a hostage will die.

08:32.960 --> 08:35.804
If you cut the feed
to my security camera...

08:35.960 --> 08:37.325
...a hostage will die.

08:37.480 --> 08:40.086
In fact the only way a hostage won't die...

08:40.240 --> 08:43.083
...is if you acquiesce to my final demand.

08:43.600 --> 08:45.967
Ryan Hardy.

08:46.120 --> 08:49.567
And if he's not here
within the next two hours...

08:49.720 --> 08:52.451
...everybody dies.

08:57.160 --> 08:58.844
[HORN HONKS]

09:19.600 --> 09:21.170
[METAL CLAN KING NEARBY]

09:25.960 --> 09:27.041
[GASPS]

09:27.200 --> 09:29.009
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

09:29.320 --> 09:30.651
THEO:
Hey.

09:31.480 --> 09:33.164
[PENNY SIGHS]

09:33.480 --> 09:35.721
He scared the crap out of me.

09:35.920 --> 09:37.445
Sorry.

09:37.600 --> 09:40.524
I didn't think you'd be awake yet.

09:44.680 --> 09:46.808
I'm assuming you gave Rehema the day off.

09:46.960 --> 09:48.450
The whole week.

09:49.520 --> 09:51.488
- Did you get... Ah.
- Of course.

09:52.720 --> 09:55.326
Thank God. Spoon?

10:08.440 --> 10:11.523
Wait. Where's Josh?

10:11.680 --> 10:12.920
Who?

10:13.080 --> 10:14.969
He was with me at the house.

10:20.200 --> 10:21.964
Did you kill him?

10:23.200 --> 10:24.725
No.

10:24.880 --> 10:26.848
Damn it.

10:27.520 --> 10:28.567
I liked him.

10:29.560 --> 10:31.562
- Heh.
- T, you can't keep doing this.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.401
- I can take care of myself.
- You're my little sister.

10:35.560 --> 10:38.882
I've been protecting you since I was 10.
I'm not gonna stop now.

10:39.040 --> 10:40.530
You need to stop partying.

10:40.680 --> 10:44.241
Yeah, says the guy with an Asian man
tied up in his study.

10:45.840 --> 10:47.569
Who the hell is he anyway?

10:47.720 --> 10:52.089
His name is Frank Sakamoto, and he's
the nation's top academic cryptologist.

10:52.240 --> 10:56.086
- And he's been completely useless.
- What's going on with you?

10:57.240 --> 10:59.527
It's not like you
to bring a kill into the house.

10:59.720 --> 11:02.121
You really don't know, do you?

11:03.480 --> 11:05.244
You haven't been watching the news?

11:11.120 --> 11:12.804
You killed Strauss?

11:15.440 --> 11:17.204
And now Ryan Hardy's after you?

11:19.080 --> 11:20.923
This is the end, T.

11:21.080 --> 11:23.401
Our cover lives are blown.

11:23.560 --> 11:25.449
They get to you, they get to me.

11:25.600 --> 11:28.285
Why do you think I pulled you in?
We need to move quickly.

11:28.440 --> 11:30.681
- What the hell are we gonna do?
- I have a plan.

11:30.840 --> 11:32.205
[PENNY SCOFFS]

11:33.560 --> 11:36.404
If it works, we can disappear.

11:38.240 --> 11:39.810
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

11:44.120 --> 11:45.406
You gotta be kidding me.

11:46.280 --> 11:47.850
PENNY:
What?

11:48.840 --> 11:51.411
It's been almost two hours
since Joe Carroll...

11:51.600 --> 11:53.523
...took hostages inside death row.

11:53.680 --> 11:55.808
Ryan Hardy and his team have arrived...

11:55.960 --> 11:57.803
...at the Virginia State Penitentiary.

11:57.960 --> 12:01.806
Hardy, of course, is one
of the most high-profile FBI agents.

12:01.960 --> 12:05.362
He apprehended Carroll
and helped put him on death row.

12:08.200 --> 12:10.601
RYAN: Where do we stand?
- Joe's made no further contact.

12:10.760 --> 12:14.162
We're ready to go. But given how he's
set up, I don't like our chances.

12:14.320 --> 12:17.164
The governor declared armed intervention
to be a last resort.

12:17.320 --> 12:20.210
He's pinning his hopes on you
defusing the situation.

12:20.360 --> 12:24.365
No way he lets me in without a search.
We don't want to increase his firepower.

12:24.560 --> 12:26.289
You can't go in unarmed.

12:28.320 --> 12:31.164
That's the only way.
I'll just need a minute.

12:31.360 --> 12:34.967
REPORTER [ON TV]:
Joe Carroll has taken hostages...

12:35.120 --> 12:36.804
...inside death row.
They just went into...

12:36.960 --> 12:38.166
[PHONE RINGS]

12:38.360 --> 12:39.964
...the FBI global command center...

12:40.120 --> 12:41.167
Ryan.

12:41.720 --> 12:45.088
- Hey.
- Please tell me you're not going in there.

12:45.440 --> 12:46.487
I have to.

12:46.640 --> 12:49.883
What if he's planning to kill you again?
When I die, you die, remember?

12:50.120 --> 12:51.645
No, Joe doesn't want me dead.

12:52.120 --> 12:54.043
He just wants a witness.

12:54.200 --> 12:56.202
I'm scared.

12:56.360 --> 12:57.521
- I gotta go.
- Wait.

13:01.120 --> 13:03.202
- I need to tell you something.
- Tell me after.

13:03.360 --> 13:05.601
- Ryan. Ryan!
- I love you.

13:11.960 --> 13:13.530
[PROTESTERS SHOUTING]

13:16.520 --> 13:20.161
WOMAN: Kill the killer!
MAN: Down with Joe Carroll!

13:21.680 --> 13:24.570
Just moments ago,
we saw FBI agent Ryan Hardy...

13:24.720 --> 13:27.690
...exit the mobile command center
and enter the main entrance...

13:27.840 --> 13:30.889
...of the prison.
- ...several hostages inside the prison.

13:31.080 --> 13:32.889
We cannot confirm who those hostages...

13:46.440 --> 13:47.771
Ryan.

13:47.920 --> 13:49.922
You get the chance, you put him down.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.889
Mike's right, kill him if you can.

13:52.040 --> 13:53.280
This has to end.

13:54.880 --> 13:56.166
If something happens...

13:57.680 --> 13:58.966
...take care of each other.

14:15.120 --> 14:16.929
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

14:34.000 --> 14:35.206
INMATE:
Where did everybody go?

14:35.360 --> 14:37.089
[INMATES SHOUTING
AND BANGING ON DOORS]

14:37.240 --> 14:39.481
Hey. You're the guy who caught Joe.

14:39.640 --> 14:40.971
What the hell is going on?

14:41.120 --> 14:42.565
[YELLING]

15:00.640 --> 15:02.529
CARROLL:
Ryan.

15:03.160 --> 15:04.650
My old friend.

15:05.640 --> 15:07.165
You came.

15:07.320 --> 15:10.051
- Take off your jacket and shirt.
- What, you don't trust me?

15:10.240 --> 15:12.208
Remove your jacket and shirt, please...

15:12.360 --> 15:14.840
...or a hostage loses an appendage.

15:28.280 --> 15:31.011
Lift it up and turn around.

15:35.840 --> 15:37.842
Good, now, there are some handcuffs...

15:38.040 --> 15:40.884
...on the floor. Can you pick them up
and cuff your hands...

15:41.080 --> 15:43.208
...behind your back?

15:43.680 --> 15:45.887
- Not until you release the hostages.
- Sorry.

15:46.880 --> 15:48.723
- No can do.
- I mean it, Joe.

15:48.920 --> 15:52.322
- They come out or I don't go in.
- May I remind you...

15:52.480 --> 15:55.723
...that you have absolutely no leverage.

15:55.880 --> 15:56.927
Sure I do.

15:57.880 --> 16:00.281
Good luck with the riot squad.

16:03.200 --> 16:06.921
Fine. Fine, fine, fine.

16:10.040 --> 16:11.724
I'll release one.

16:15.000 --> 16:17.241
No sudden movements.

16:17.400 --> 16:18.447
[BRADLEY WHIMPERING]

16:18.600 --> 16:20.602
Well done.

16:27.520 --> 16:30.683
There's a team waiting by the entrance,
they'll take you out. Go.

16:58.560 --> 17:00.130
[GRUNTS]

17:02.240 --> 17:05.449
Now, if you'd only RSVP'd yes
to my execution...

17:05.599 --> 17:07.602
...none of this would've been necessary.

17:16.319 --> 17:18.846
THEO: This was Strauss' journal.
It's a new cypher.

17:19.040 --> 17:22.931
One I've never seen before.
Some kind of polyalphabetic substitution.

17:23.079 --> 17:25.924
- Saka-what's-his-name can't figure it out?
- Sakamoto.

17:26.079 --> 17:28.970
No. The key is a phrase, but it's long.

17:29.120 --> 17:31.646
Without knowing the source,
it's impossible to crack.

17:31.800 --> 17:34.610
- Why do you need this? What's in it?
- A name.

17:34.760 --> 17:37.969
Someone with the power
to give me my anonymity back.

17:39.960 --> 17:42.167
After I take out Ryan Hardy.

17:42.320 --> 17:45.483
Are you kidding?
He caught Strauss and Joe Carroll.

17:45.640 --> 17:48.086
- You need to leave him alone.
- Not an option.

17:48.240 --> 17:49.480
[SCOFFS]

17:50.360 --> 17:52.966
That's your problem, T.
You always have to win.

17:53.120 --> 17:55.009
And we're alive because of it.

17:55.160 --> 17:59.131
Because I do whatever it takes
to give us what we never had as kids.

17:59.280 --> 18:00.486
Control.

18:01.640 --> 18:02.846
And I love you for it.

18:03.480 --> 18:06.723
But taking on Ryan Hardy
and the FBI is crazy.

18:06.880 --> 18:10.202
I will make him suffer for what he's done.

18:10.680 --> 18:13.081
I think Joe Carroll
might be taking care of that.

18:29.680 --> 18:31.364
- Hey.

18:32.720 --> 18:35.883
- You're awake.
- What am I doing here, Joe?

18:36.040 --> 18:37.246
Up.

18:37.400 --> 18:38.765
Up' up, Up.

18:42.400 --> 18:45.927
What does it always come down
to with us, huh? The truth.

18:46.240 --> 18:50.689
You can fool everyone else,
but you can't fool me.

18:50.840 --> 18:53.207
I can quite clearly see that...

18:53.400 --> 18:56.449
That you are a man in crisis.
I mean, you could...

18:56.640 --> 18:59.086
...hide behind that macho
facade of yours...

18:59.280 --> 19:01.203
...but you're suffering.

19:01.360 --> 19:04.045
- And I know why.
- So do I.

19:04.360 --> 19:05.407
You.

19:05.560 --> 19:06.607
[SCOFFS]

19:06.760 --> 19:09.240
You so desperately want that to be true.

19:09.400 --> 19:12.131
That way, you don't have to face
the reality of what you...

19:12.280 --> 19:15.602
...fight so slavishly every day to deny.

19:15.760 --> 19:18.809
- And what reality is that?
- That I am your soul mate.

19:19.000 --> 19:20.365
[SCOFFS]

19:20.640 --> 19:23.291
- Check, please.
- Oh, you can mock, yes.

19:23.440 --> 19:26.603
Mock all you like.
But if that's not true...

19:26.760 --> 19:29.809
...then why didn't you kill me
when you had the chance?

19:29.960 --> 19:32.361
Oh, please, don't give me
any of that kumbaya...

19:32.560 --> 19:34.927
did it to save my soul" nonsense.

19:35.080 --> 19:38.129
You didn't kill me because you need me.

19:38.320 --> 19:40.766
And I would be a terrible friend
if I didn't use...

19:40.920 --> 19:44.322
...what precious little time I have left
to help you see that.

19:44.920 --> 19:48.322
So you ask why you're here?

19:48.480 --> 19:50.130
Well, today...

19:50.280 --> 19:52.282
...I'm gonna stage an intervention.

19:52.440 --> 19:55.171
And when I'm done,
all you have hidden...

19:55.320 --> 19:57.607
...will be exposed. Because today...

19:57.760 --> 20:01.446
...you will admit that I am the most
important relationship in your life.

20:01.600 --> 20:03.841
Not because you think
that's what I wanna hear...

20:04.000 --> 20:06.287
...but because you know...

20:06.440 --> 20:09.284
...deep in your heart...

20:10.240 --> 20:11.969
...that it's true.

20:13.200 --> 20:14.850
And if you don't...

20:15.000 --> 20:16.286
...we're all gonna die.

20:25.160 --> 20:26.321
You Okay?

20:26.480 --> 20:28.005
Not really.

20:29.760 --> 20:32.650
- If I lose Ryan...
- He's gonna be okay.

20:33.960 --> 20:35.724
And I'll always be there for you.

20:38.040 --> 20:40.247
Whether you like it or not.

20:42.520 --> 20:45.842
Hey. The warden just got off the phone
with the governor.

20:46.000 --> 20:48.651
He's changed his mind about waiting.
We're getting ready.

20:48.800 --> 20:50.882
Joe will kill them.
We need to give Ryan time.

20:51.040 --> 20:54.249
He's got 10 minutes.
After that, it's out of my hands.

20:57.240 --> 21:00.687
Come on, Joe. This is between us.
Let them go.

21:01.320 --> 21:05.689
No. They form a vital part
of your intervention.

21:10.160 --> 21:11.207
Now...

21:11.360 --> 21:12.850
[BOTH WHIMPERING]

21:14.400 --> 21:16.209
Jump down.

21:16.360 --> 21:18.522
There we are.
Just jump down there, darling.

21:19.680 --> 21:22.365
Now, Mr. Vail, would you be so kind
as to strap Dana...

21:22.520 --> 21:24.887
...to the examination table?

21:25.040 --> 21:27.520
- Why?
- Because I said so.

21:31.280 --> 21:33.567
Joe, what are you doing?

21:33.720 --> 21:35.085
I thought this was about me.

21:35.280 --> 21:38.045
It is, but that's no reason
why I can't enjoy myself too.

21:39.680 --> 21:41.523
[SOBBING]

21:46.080 --> 21:49.448
Now, Mr. Vail, would you mind
standing by the desk?

21:52.320 --> 21:53.606
Okay, okay.

21:53.800 --> 21:55.245
So help me see the truth.

21:55.400 --> 21:57.767
- What am I denying?
CARROLL: You have always been...

21:57.960 --> 22:01.442
...my most devoted follower.

22:01.600 --> 22:05.400
No one else has ever felt
as passionately about me as you.

22:05.560 --> 22:08.928
- I was trying to stop you.
- And in trying to stop me...

22:09.080 --> 22:11.287
...you became me.

22:11.440 --> 22:13.442
No, I'm not like you, Joe.

22:13.640 --> 22:16.291
I don't have a need to kill.

22:16.480 --> 22:18.926
I think your body count
might say otherwise.

22:19.080 --> 22:20.923
If I didn't pull that trigger...

22:21.080 --> 22:24.448
...innocent people would die.
I saved lives.

22:24.600 --> 22:26.648
Oh, boy. No, this is just going nowhere.

22:26.840 --> 22:28.604
I'm gonna have to take it up a notch.

22:28.760 --> 22:32.321
Dana, darling, I'm gonna take out
your eyes now.

22:32.480 --> 22:35.086
- Wait! Wait, wait, no! No, wait!
- Please! No, please!

22:35.240 --> 22:37.288
- Make me.
- When I first came to see you...

22:37.440 --> 22:39.966
...you asked me if you were in my dreams.

22:43.120 --> 22:44.645
You are.

22:47.920 --> 22:48.967
In what capacity?

22:49.120 --> 22:50.360
[WHIMPERING]

22:50.520 --> 22:52.204
In...

22:52.920 --> 22:54.968
In my dreams...

22:57.000 --> 22:58.650
...we're friends.

22:59.800 --> 23:03.646
We drink together.

23:04.960 --> 23:06.530
And?

23:09.280 --> 23:11.203
And you're teaching me to kill.

23:21.840 --> 23:23.171
Oh.

23:26.640 --> 23:27.926
I'm proud of you, Ryan.

23:34.120 --> 23:36.168
That couldn't have been easy to admit.

23:40.160 --> 23:42.561
What do you think
your dreams are telling you?

23:42.720 --> 23:44.563
- That you screwed up my head.
- No, no.

23:44.720 --> 23:48.167
I think they're telling you
that we are friends.

23:49.160 --> 23:50.241
Best of friends.

23:51.840 --> 23:55.686
You... You see me for who I really am...

23:55.840 --> 23:58.730
...as I see you for who you really are.

24:00.520 --> 24:05.003
- You don't know me.
- Oh, come on, Ryan.

24:05.960 --> 24:09.203
You know that's a lie.

24:09.360 --> 24:12.409
I am the only one...

24:12.560 --> 24:13.971
...who knows the real you.

24:16.840 --> 24:18.683
Now, come on.

24:18.840 --> 24:20.683
Tell me...

24:21.880 --> 24:25.168
...what are you so afraid of?

24:26.760 --> 24:28.762
That you're right.

24:29.480 --> 24:31.369
Well, of course I am.

24:33.400 --> 24:36.882
Don't tell me that you didn't enjoy
killing the man...

24:37.040 --> 24:38.451
...who murdered your father.

24:38.600 --> 24:40.090
Or Debra Parker's killer.

24:41.280 --> 24:43.886
- No.
- Well, then what?

24:45.080 --> 24:46.889
Come on, Ryan.

24:47.040 --> 24:49.566
Confess what you know to be true.

24:49.720 --> 24:51.961
What did you get...

24:52.120 --> 24:54.805
...out of pulling that trigger?

24:58.760 --> 25:00.888
Satisfaction.

25:05.600 --> 25:07.090
Power.

25:10.760 --> 25:13.411
And that's what felt good.

25:15.080 --> 25:17.162
Thank you, Ryan.

25:17.760 --> 25:20.161
That's all I was looking for.

25:23.600 --> 25:26.285
Just a little bit of honesty.

25:44.560 --> 25:47.040
I can accept my fate...

25:47.800 --> 25:50.849
...because you have finally admitted...

25:51.760 --> 25:53.808
...that I'm right.

25:55.960 --> 25:57.644
[CARROLL GRUNTS]

25:57.800 --> 25:59.609
[COUGHS THEN GRUNTS]

25:59.760 --> 26:01.205
Whew.

26:02.960 --> 26:04.485
Ah.

26:08.800 --> 26:11.007
You win, Joe.

26:20.920 --> 26:21.967
PENNY:
What are you doing?

26:22.120 --> 26:25.841
Trying to get a look inside the prison.
I hid a back door in their server.

26:26.400 --> 26:28.323
I gotta hand it to Joe.

26:28.520 --> 26:30.682
The guy knows how to make an exit.

26:32.120 --> 26:33.326
What are those?

26:35.520 --> 26:37.170
Controls for the prison.

26:37.360 --> 26:39.203
From here I can do anything I want...

26:39.360 --> 26:42.204
...turn off the cameras, open the doors.

26:42.520 --> 26:45.330
If I wanted to,
I could lock the whole place down.

26:51.080 --> 26:54.368
...Whether or not this was all part
of Joe Carroll's plan.

26:57.560 --> 26:59.881
Hey, wait a minute.
Something's happening.

27:00.880 --> 27:02.530
It's Ryan, he did it.

27:05.080 --> 27:08.527
- What are you doing?
- Protecting you from yourself.

27:09.880 --> 27:11.370
[INMATES SHOUTING]

27:11.560 --> 27:13.210
[DOOR LOCKS BUZZ]

27:19.760 --> 27:22.764
- Wait, who the hell opened those doors?
COMMANDER: It wasn't us.

27:22.960 --> 27:24.564
Hey, we need to get in there now.

27:24.760 --> 27:25.807
Open the damn doors.

27:26.240 --> 27:28.083
Can't, the whole system just went down.

27:32.080 --> 27:35.482
Damn. I guess karma really does exist.

27:38.080 --> 27:39.525
Back up. Back the hell up!

27:39.680 --> 27:41.011
[GRUNTING AND YELLING]

27:57.200 --> 27:59.601
We should do a little hostage-taking
of our own.

27:59.760 --> 28:02.570
Knock yourselves out.
Joe's gonna show me his cell.

28:02.720 --> 28:06.725
The one he doesn't think I'm good enough
for. I wanna redecorate it with his brains.

28:06.880 --> 28:09.121
That's not actually what
brains are for, but...

28:15.080 --> 28:16.491
Get behind me.

28:16.640 --> 28:18.847
Hey, baby, come here,
let me get a look at you.

28:19.040 --> 28:20.280
VAIL: Hey.
DANA: No.

28:20.440 --> 28:21.930
- Aah!

28:23.160 --> 28:25.561
It's cool, do what you gotta do.

28:25.760 --> 28:27.683
- Think we need your permission?
- What? No.

28:28.760 --> 28:30.410
What are you doing? Don't kill him.

28:31.720 --> 28:32.721
[GRUNTS]

28:33.320 --> 28:34.810
[GRUNTING]

28:39.640 --> 28:40.971
[GASPING]

28:42.920 --> 28:44.490
Just keep pressure on it.

28:49.920 --> 28:52.161
VAIL:
Wait, where are you going?

28:52.320 --> 28:54.288
Wait, you can't leave me.

28:55.440 --> 28:57.010
[DANA SHRIEKING AND WHIMPERING]

29:02.040 --> 29:03.644
[SOBBING]

29:04.640 --> 29:07.291
Stop. No, please stop.

29:07.800 --> 29:08.847
No!

29:09.000 --> 29:10.331
[SCREAMING]

29:12.360 --> 29:14.089
Help!

29:15.840 --> 29:17.126
[YELLS]

29:39.480 --> 29:42.245
It's okay. You're safe now.

29:48.440 --> 29:49.726
[SOBBING]

30:01.160 --> 30:02.207
Get.

30:03.840 --> 30:04.921
Fancy.

30:05.840 --> 30:07.842
- Yeah.
- You're an eye guy, right?

30:08.000 --> 30:09.445
No, calling me an eye guy...

30:09.640 --> 30:12.405
...is like calling Rembrandt a decorator.

30:12.560 --> 30:14.403
Who the hell's Rembrandt?

30:14.560 --> 30:16.244
[GRUNTING]

30:56.760 --> 30:58.410
[PANTING]

31:01.560 --> 31:03.244
Come on, come on.

31:04.560 --> 31:06.210
OFFICER:
Okay. Move, come on.

31:24.800 --> 31:26.131
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

31:28.600 --> 31:30.250
OFFICER:
Move in.

31:36.840 --> 31:39.161
Thank God. Are you okay?

31:41.320 --> 31:43.004
Yeah, I'm good.

31:51.600 --> 31:55.889
We can report the hostage crisis inside
the Virginia State Penitentiary is over.

31:56.040 --> 31:58.441
The number of casualties still unknown.

31:58.640 --> 32:02.247
The FBI has yet to confirm the names
of those killed inside the prison...

32:02.440 --> 32:04.124
Hostage crisis is over.

32:04.320 --> 32:06.163
Looks like Joe and Ryan both survived.

32:06.360 --> 32:09.443
You have no idea what you almost did.
You almost blew this thing.

32:09.640 --> 32:10.801
You can big-brother me...

32:10.960 --> 32:15.522
...kill my boyfriends, criticize my life choices.
And if I try to look after you, I'm out of line?

32:15.880 --> 32:18.884
- Penny... - You need to drop
this Ryan Hardy nonsense.

32:19.920 --> 32:21.410
If this contact can help us...

32:21.560 --> 32:24.769
...let's crack the code, go to him.
You and me, we disappear together.

32:24.960 --> 32:27.611
You don't get it,
he won't do it voluntarily.

32:27.840 --> 32:29.490
I need leverage to make it happen.

32:29.640 --> 32:31.005
What kind of leverage?

32:32.720 --> 32:33.846
Him.

32:35.200 --> 32:38.727
His death is the key to our future.

32:44.160 --> 32:45.650
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

32:45.800 --> 32:47.165
[SIGHS]

32:47.360 --> 32:49.362
- Are you okay?
RYAN: Yeah.

32:49.920 --> 32:51.365
It's over.

32:52.960 --> 32:55.691
- Is Joe dead?
- No.

32:55.840 --> 32:59.845
I don't know what's gonna happen with his
execution, but I need to stick around to see.

33:00.000 --> 33:01.365
What? Are you kidding?

33:03.840 --> 33:05.524
I need to get closure on this, Gwen.

33:06.840 --> 33:09.320
I don't expect you to understand.

33:09.480 --> 33:12.324
Good. I don't, it seems like
you're giving him what he wants.

33:12.480 --> 33:14.369
You told me you could handle anything.

33:15.360 --> 33:17.488
I need you to handle this.

33:23.000 --> 33:25.890
PENNY: You're a genius hacker.
A code is like the ultimate password.

33:26.040 --> 33:27.690
How do you hack someone's password?

33:27.880 --> 33:30.770
- Study them, understand what's important.
- Same thing here.

33:30.920 --> 33:33.082
He wouldn't pick a random phrase,
he would've picked...

33:33.280 --> 33:35.726
...from a source that meant something.
- Gotta be a book.

33:35.880 --> 33:38.724
I looked through the books the FBI took
from his house. None work.

33:38.880 --> 33:42.601
He wouldn't have kept it in his house.
You said you went to Joe, why?

33:42.760 --> 33:44.888
Because Joe knew Strauss
better than anyone.

33:46.560 --> 33:48.642
- And you checked Joe's books?
- Yes.

33:48.800 --> 33:51.326
All the books that they had in common.

33:53.800 --> 33:57.771
But I should've checked the books in Joe's
library that Strauss should've had in his.

34:01.040 --> 34:03.441
Lovecraft. Strauss quoted him a few times.
Let's see.

34:06.760 --> 34:09.081
"That is not dead which can eternal lie

34:09.239 --> 34:13.085
And with strange aeons
even death may die."

34:22.480 --> 34:24.322
It's working.

34:27.960 --> 34:29.371
Come on.

34:32.280 --> 34:33.884
T, that's not a name.

34:37.280 --> 34:38.850
No.

34:40.520 --> 34:43.170
- It's a location.
REPORTER: The nation holds its breath...

34:43.320 --> 34:45.641
...as we wait for word
on the governor's decision.

34:45.800 --> 34:50.168
Our legal experts predict he'll have no
choice but to postpone Carroll's execution.

34:50.320 --> 34:52.368
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

35:05.000 --> 35:06.525
Why?

35:07.880 --> 35:09.644
Why did today have to happen?

35:11.720 --> 35:15.042
Because you are my real legacy, Ryan.

35:16.000 --> 35:18.651
And I needed you to know it.

35:19.320 --> 35:23.962
And now that you admitted...

35:24.120 --> 35:25.167
...we are brothers...

35:26.840 --> 35:28.922
...I can die...

35:29.560 --> 35:34.282
...knowing that I will live on
through you.

35:39.240 --> 35:42.801
The governor's ordered your execution
to proceed as scheduled.

35:44.000 --> 35:46.162
They're coming to take you
in a few minutes.

35:46.840 --> 35:47.887
Uh, Ryan.

35:54.080 --> 35:55.570
A parting gift:

35:56.920 --> 35:59.400
Your man, Theo...

36:00.080 --> 36:02.162
...he was born of violence...

36:04.520 --> 36:07.649
...in the city of brotherly love.

36:12.240 --> 36:13.969
Goodbye, Joe.

36:16.160 --> 36:18.686
Goodbye, Ryan.

36:19.000 --> 36:20.729
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

36:46.400 --> 36:47.606
[DOOR BUZZES THEN OPENS]

38:24.920 --> 38:26.126
WARDEN:
Joe Carroll.

38:26.320 --> 38:29.529
The state of Virginia has sentenced you
to die for your many crimes.

38:29.880 --> 38:31.882
You have any final words?

38:42.720 --> 38:45.291
Quoth the Raven

38:46.640 --> 38:48.369
"Nevermore."

39:11.280 --> 39:12.566
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

39:14.000 --> 39:15.650
[GRUNTING]

39:30.840 --> 39:32.410
[CONTINUES GRUNTING]

39:57.760 --> 39:59.489
[GROANING]

40:32.160 --> 40:33.650
[BEEPING]

40:47.480 --> 40:50.211
Time of death is 12:11 a.m.

41:00.040 --> 41:02.247
[SHUTTER MECHANISM WHIRRING]

41:25.040 --> 41:27.042
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]
[CHATTERING]

41:42.360 --> 41:44.488
- Hi.
- Hi.

41:44.640 --> 41:46.051
Bad day?

41:55.720 --> 41:58.371
Two shots of whiskey, please.

42:12.400 --> 42:14.846
Hope it helps.

42:23.400 --> 42:25.402
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

42:43.160 --> 42:44.571
Here's to you.

42:44.760 --> 42:48.128
No. Here's to us.

43:13.080 --> 43:14.684
Again.

43:57.960 --> 43:59.962
[English - US - SDH]
